text.section:
An application for an arrest warrant under this section shall be:
In writing;
Signed and sworn to by the law enforcement officer; and
Accompanied by an affidavit that sets forth the basis for there being probable cause to believe that:
The child who is the subject of the warrant has committed a delinquent act; and
Unless the child who is the subject of the warrant is taken into custody, the child:
Is likely to leave the jurisdiction of the court;
May not be apprehended;
May cause physical injury or property damage to another; or
May tamper with, dispose of, or destroy evidence.
